; maize-14: mzdis reserved/unassigned-opcode-byte resync fixture (AC6481).
;
; HALT, then two reserved bytes ($37, $38 -- both still explicitly "reserved")
; embedded via DATA (a raw byte literal, not
; an instruction), then a valid instruction (NOP), then HALT. mzdis must decode
; each reserved byte as its own "DB $XX ; unknown opcode" line, advancing
; exactly one byte each time, and resume correct decoding at NOP. ($21 was a
; reserved byte historically but is FDIV as of maize-122; $37/$38 are reserved
; slots that stay unallocated. $93 was reserved historically but is LDZ as of
; maize-204, so it is no longer a resync fixture byte.)

HALT
DATA $37
DATA $38
NOP
HALT
